'''Rya Kirsch''' was one of the pilots who led the assault on the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]] [[Lucrehulk-class battleship/Legends|Droid Control Ship]] during the [[Battle of Naboo/Legends|Battle of Naboo]] in [[32 BBY]].

==Biography==
Rya originally flew recon missions for the [[Royal Naboo Security Forces/Legends|Royal Naboo Security Forces]] before joining [[Bravo Squadron/Legends|Bravo Flight]] under the command of [[Ric Olié/Legends|Ric Olié]]. He later became an expert in starfighter defensive aviation tactics.

Having achieved the rank of [[Lieutenant/Legends|lieutenant]], Kirsch flew as '''[[Bravo Four]]''' during the [[Battle of Naboo]], and entered into combat against an attack fleet of [[Vulture-class starfighter/Legends|Vulture droids]] during an ambush against the [[Lucrehulk-class battleship/Legends|Droid Control Ship]] [[Vuutun Palaa/Legends|''Vuutun Palaa'']]. After joining [[Ric Olié/Legends|Ric Olié]] in an attack run, Kirsch was killed when the ''Vuntunn Palaa''{{'s}} [[Turbolaser/Legends|turbolasers]] shot down his starfighter.

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:JohnKnoll-TPM.jpg|thumb|220px|John Knoll on set]]
This character, played by [[Industrial Light & Magic|ILM]] Visual Effects Supervisor [[John Knoll]], continues the tradition of the in-cockpit death scene featured in several ''Star Wars'' space/air battles. Rya Kirsch is sometimes known as "Jet Porkins"&mdash;a reference to the pilot [[Jek Tono Porkins/Legends|Jek Porkins]], who had the first in-cockpit death during [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']].

Knoll also plays a Naboo flag bearer during the parade in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''The Phantom Menace'']], and the roles of a firespeeder pilot and opera house patron [[Tannon Praji/Legends|Tannon Praji]] in [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Revenge of the Sith'']].

